<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-158-954  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 158 954.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hey Super Mario--how about a Super Bowl? (Nintendo nationwideplayoff)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Nintendo Company Ltd. (marketing).andO;Product:   Nintendo Entertainment System (Computer system) (competitions).andO;Topic:     Video GamesComputer gamesMarketing StrategyPromotion of ProductContests.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HEY SUPER MARIO--HOW ABOUT A SUPER BOWL? DALLAS, TEXAS, U.S.A., 1990, FEB 1(NB) -- Nintendo enthusiasts will be able to test their skills during anationwide playoff that begins in Dallas March 8 to 11 and is expected toinvolve some 1.2 million contestants as it moves to 29 additional cities inthe United States and Canada.andM;Danny Eaton, a promoter located in Dallas, has dubbed the event the &quot;SuperBowl&quot; of video games.andP;  When the city by city tour is completed, seven winnersfrom each city will compete for the championship at a contest in Orlando, FLscheduled for late October.andM;Prizes will include a five-figure savings bond, a car and a lifetime supplyof Nintendo software.andP;  Contestants will pay a $3 entry fee in addition toadmission charges and will be treated to a sneak preview of new Nintendosoftware.andP;  For those who attend but are not competitors, Nintendo will supplyeach event with games to try.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900207)</TEXT></DOC>